The Chronicle Nqobile Tshili, Chronicle Reporter AN Umzingwane District-born businessman has engaged Government to inject US$150 million to rehabilitate 120KM Old Gwanda Road under a build, operate and transfer (BOT) arrangement. Engineer Bekithemba Mbambo who runs Zwane Enterprises said he has an American partner and they obtained a bank guarantee for the project. He said his company is headquartered in Harare.
Old Gwanda Road passes through Matopo High School and motorists have decried the state of the road. <img class="size-large wp-image-687743" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/vedgbxcv-680x380.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/vedgbxcv.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2023/03/vedgbxcv-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Eng Mbambo said coming from Silobi area under Chief Mathe, he has had first-hand experience on the state of the road hence it was dear for him to have the road fixed.